   "source": [
    "# Inferring coupling strengths from configuration of variables\n",
    "# Method: Free Energy Minimization (FEM)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import sys\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import myfunction as mf\n",
    "#import meanfield as meanfield\n",
    "import fem as fem\n",
    "import myplot as mp\n",
    "\n",
    "np.random.seed(1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# parameter:\n",
    "n = 100    # number of variables\n",
    "\n",
    "def check_performance(g,l):    \n",
    "    # simulate data:\n",
    "    w0,s0 = mf.simulate_data(n,g,l)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # recover couplings from observed data s0 by using Free Energy Minimization (FEM)\n",
    "    wFEM = fem.fit_interaction(s0)\n",
    "    mp.plot_w(w0,wFEM)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 1. Large sample size ($l = N^2$)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "l = n**2  # data length"

  },
  {

   "metadata": {},
